Title: Object: Le repos en Egypte
Series: Galerie du Palais Royal
Description: Rest on the flight into Egypt, after Barocci; the Virgin dips a bowl into a pool of water as Joseph and Jesus play with a tree branch with berries; the donkey stands at left; with engraved text below. c.1786/1808 Etching and engraving, with image printed from a separate plate
Curator's comments: From 'Galerie du Palais Royal', a set published between 1786 and 1808; see 1837,0408.317 for comment. After a painting by Barocci known through several versions, see A. Emiliani, 'Federico Barocci', 1985, volume I, pages 78-85
Acquisition name: Purchased from: A E Evans & Sons
